<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">

 <head>

  <title>CSS Test: separated borders model - rules="all"</title>
  <link rel="author" title="GÃ©rard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/tables.html#separated-borders" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/struct/tables.html#adef-rules" />
  <meta name="flags" content="" />
  <meta name="assert" content="In the border-collapse separate model, each cell has an individual border. The rules attribute defines which rules to draw between cells." />

  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
  table
  {
  background-color: yellow;
  border: outset 1px;
  border-collapse: separate;
  border-spacing: 48px;
  }

  td
  {
  height: 64px;
  width: 64px;
  }
  ]]></style>

 </head>

 <body>

  <p>Below there should be a big yellow square. Inside such big yellow square, there must be 4 smaller squares spaced apart from each other.</p>

  <table rules="all">
   <tr>
    <td></td>
    <td></td>
   </tr>

   <tr>
    <td></td>
    <td></td>
   </tr>
  </table>

 </body>
</html>